		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "An update for servicemesh-proxy is now available for OpenShift Service Mesh 1.0.\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Important. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.",
				"title": "Topic"
			},
			{
				"category": "general",
				"text": "Red Hat OpenShift Service Mesh is Red Hat's distribution of the Istio service mesh project, tailored for installation into an on-premise OpenShift Container Platform installation.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* nghttp2: overly large SETTINGS frames can lead to DoS (CVE-2020-11080)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
				"title": "Details"
			},
